name: janus caeruleum
description:
when exploring the wild beaches in albania during the summer of 2013 this unique setting caught my eyes and prompted me to run back a couple of kms to fetch my canon single-lens reflex. arriving back on site, it took me 20 min to catch what i wanted to capture. years later i am still unsure what it is that i caught. 

opensea.

4272x2752px. none-edited except colours and crop.
